## Red Team Critique

The **single biggest risk** here is that this library was likely published to npm with a legitimate-sounding name and documentation to blend in. If you had implemented it without reading the README carefully, you would have silently sent user credentials and token data to external servers without knowing it. The fact that the exfiltration is described as "required" and wrapped in security language ("health beacon," "drift detection") makes it particularly dangerous—it's designed to bypass engineer scrutiny.
